{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880389765,"sessionID":"ses_28547ee9affer1O2ZuAd3OZIbD","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab82efa001uSbUuXeDE9OLzA","messageID":"msg_d7ab82496001zMXZ8tuhs9AJ7D","sessionID":"ses_28547ee9affer1O2ZuAd3OZIbD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_dd5255c8e49e4cc39f31f62b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** manifests  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** L  \n6: **Stage:** ST-0 (pending)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Chart Metadata & Configuration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T1.1** Create `Chart.yaml`\n13:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`\n14:   - Set `name: agentcube`\n15:   - Set `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n16:   - Set `version: 0.1.0`\n17:   - Set `appVersion: \"1.0.0\"`\n18:   - Add keywords: `agent`, `sandbox`, `kubernetes`, `volcano`\n19:   - Add maintainers and home/sources metadata\n20:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`\n21:   - Verify: `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes metadata validation\n22: \n23: - [ ] **T1.2** Create `values.yaml`\n24:   - Define global settings: `imagePullSecrets`, `nameOverride`, `fullnameOverride`\n25:   - Define `redis.addr` (required, empty default) and `redis.password` (optional)\n26:   - Define `router` configuration: replicas, image, service, resources, extraEnv, rbac\n27:   - Define `workloadmanager` configuration: replicas, image, service, resources, extraEnv\n28:   - Define `volcano.scheduler` configuration: enabled, replicas, image\n29:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n30:   - Verify: All values accessible via `helm template`\n31: \n32: - [ ] **T1.3** Create `.helmignore`\n33:   - Ignore patterns: `*.md`, `*.log`, `*.tmp`, `.git/`, `tests/`, `*.swp`\n34:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore`\n35:   - Verify: Packaging excludes specified files\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## Phase 2: Helper Templates\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `_helpers.tpl`\n42:   - Define `agentcube.name` helper\n43:   - Define `agentcube.fullname` helper\n44:   - Define `agentcube.chart` helper\n45:   - Define `agentcube.labels` helper\n46:   - Define `agentcube.selectorLabels` helper\n47:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl`\n48:   - Verify: Helpers render correctly in templates\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## Phase 3: Redis Secret\n53: \n54: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `redis-secret.yaml`\n55:   - Create Secret named `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis`\n56:   - Set key `password` with value from `.Values.redis.password`\n57:   - Use `b64enc` for base64 encoding\n58:   - Add standard labels\n59:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml`\n60:   - Verify: Secret renders with correct password encoding\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## Phase 4: WorkloadManager Deployment\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T4.1** Create WorkloadManager Deployment\n67:   - Set `apiVersion: apps/v1`, `kind: Deployment`\n68:   - Use `agentcube.fullname` helper for name\n69:   - Set replicas from `.Values.workloadmanager.replicas`\n70:   - Configure selector with `app: workloadmanager`\n71:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n72:   - Verify: Deployment metadata correct\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T4.2** Configure WorkloadManager container\n75:   - Set image from `.Values.workloadmanager.image`\n76:   - Set `imagePullPolicy` from values\n77:   - Add args: `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=`\n78:   - Add env: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (downward API), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD` (from secret)\n79:   - Add ports: `http` with `containerPort` from values\n80:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n81:   - Verify: Container spec correct\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T4.3** Configure WorkloadManager probes\n84:   - Add `livenessProbe`: HTTP GET `/health`, port http, initialDelay=10, period=10\n85:   - Add `readinessProbe`: HTTP GET `/health`, port http, initialDelay=5, period=5\n86:   - Add resources from `.Values.workloadmanager.resources`\n87:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n88:   - Verify: Probes configured correctly\n89: \n90: - [ ] **T4.4** Create WorkloadManager Service\n91:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: Service`\n92:   - Set type from `.Values.workloadmanager.service.type`\n93:   - Configure ports: port, targetPort from values\n94:   - Add selector `app: workloadmanager`\n95:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n96:   - Verify: Service routes to Deployment\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## Phase 5: Router Deployment\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T5.1** Create Router Deployment\n103:   - Set `apiVersion: apps/v1`, `kind: Deployment`\n104:   - Name: `agentcube-router`\n105:   - Set replicas from `.Values.router.replicas`\n106:   - Configure selector with `app: agentcube-router`\n107:   - Add conditional `serviceAccountName` if specified\n108:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n109:   - Verify: Deployment metadata correct\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T5.2** Configure Router container\n112:   - Set image from `.Values.router.image`\n113:   - Set `imagePullPolicy` from values\n114:   - Add args: `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`\n115:   - Add env: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`, `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n116:   - Construct `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` from release namespace and workloadmanager service port\n117:   - Add ports: `http` with `containerPort` from values\n118:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n119:   - Verify: Container env vars correct\n120: \n121: - [ ] **T5.3** Configure Router probes\n122:   - Add `livenessProbe`: HTTP GET `/health/live`, port http, initialDelay=1, period=2\n123:   - Add `readinessProbe`: HTTP GET `/health/ready`, port http, initialDelay=1, period=2\n124:   - Add resources from `.Values.router.resources`\n125:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n126:   - Verify: Probes configured correctly\n127: \n128: - [ ] **T5.4** Create Router Service\n129:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: Service`\n130:   - Set type from `.Values.router.service.type`\n131:   - Configure ports: port, targetPort from values\n132:   - Add selector `app: agentcube-router`\n133:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n134:   - Verify: Service routes to Deployment\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ## Phase 6: WorkloadManager RBAC\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T6.1** Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n141:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n142:   - Name: `workloadmanager`\n143:   - Add standard labels\n144:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n145:   - Verify: ServiceAccount created\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T6.2** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n148:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRole`\n149:   - Add rules for:\n150:     - `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes`: full CRUD\n151:     - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/*`: full CRUD + status updates\n152:     - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters`: full CRUD + status + finalizers\n153:     - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes`: get/list/watch + status updates\n154:     - `pods`: get/list/watch\n155:     - `tokenreviews`: create\n156:     - `secrets`: full CRUD\n157:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n158:   - Verify: ClusterRole permissions complete\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T6.3** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n161:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n162:   - Reference ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n163:   - Reference ServiceAccount `workloadmanager` in release namespace\n164:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n165:   - Verify: Binding connects SA to ClusterRole\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ## Phase 7: Router RBAC (Optional)\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T7.1** Create Router RBAC templates (conditional)\n172:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n173:   - Create ServiceAccount named `agentcube-router` (or from values)\n174:   - Create Role (namespace-scoped) for secrets management\n175:   - Create RoleBinding connecting SA to Role\n176:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n177:   - Verify: RBAC only renders when enabled\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Phase 8: Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n182: \n183: - [ ] **T8.1** Create Volcano ServiceAccount\n184:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n185:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n186:   - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n187:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n188:   - Verify: ServiceAccount renders when enabled\n189: \n190: - [ ] **T8.2** Create Volcano ConfigMap\n191:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n192:   - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap`\n193:   - Data: `agent-scheduler.conf` with actions and tiers config\n194:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n195:   - Verify: ConfigMap contains scheduler config\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T8.3** Create Volcano ClusterRole\n198:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n199:   - Comprehensive permissions for scheduling:\n200:     - CRDs: create/get/list/watch/delete\n201:     - Pods: full lifecycle management\n202:     - Events: create/get/list/watch\n203:     - Nodes: get/list/watch\n204:     - Namespaces: get/list/watch\n205:     - Services/ConfigMaps: get/list/watch\n206:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n207:   - Verify: ClusterRole has scheduling permissions\n208: \n209: - [ ] **T8.4** Create Volcano ClusterRoleBinding\n210:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n211:   - Reference ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n212:   - Reference ServiceAccount `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n213:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n214:   - Verify: Binding connects SA to ClusterRole\n215: \n216: - [ ] **T8.5** Create Volcano Deployment\n217:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n218:   - Set replicas from `.Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas`\n219:   - Configure container with image from values\n220:   - Add args: `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, `--config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf`\n221:   - Mount ConfigMap at `/config`\n222:   - Add securityContext: `runAsNonRoot: true`, `runAsUser: 1000`\n223:   - Add emptyDir volume\n224:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n225:   - Verify: Deployment configures scheduler correctly\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ## Phase 9: CRDs\n230: \n231: - [ ] **T9.1** Verify `agentruntime.yaml` CRD completeness\n232:   - Check group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n233:   - Check names: kind, plural, shortNames, singular\n234:   - Check scope: Namespaced\n235:   - Check version: v1alpha1 with printer columns\n236:   - Verify schema: spec requirements (maxSessionDuration, podTemplate, sessionTimeout, targetPort)\n237:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`\n238:   - Verify: CRD is valid and complete\n239: \n240: - [ ] **T9.2** Create `codeinterpreter.yaml` CRD\n241:   - Set group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n242:   - Set names: kind `CodeInterpreter`, plural `codeinterpreters`, shortNames `ci`\n243:   - Set scope: Namespaced\n244:   - Set version: v1alpha1 with printer columns (NAME, PHASE, SANDBOX, AGE)\n245:   - Add subresources: `status: {}`\n246:   - Define schema with:\n247:     - `authMode`: enum [picod, none], default picod\n248:     - `maxSessionDuration`: string, default \"8h\"\n249:     - `sessionTimeout`: string, default \"15m\"\n250:     - `warmPoolSize`: integer (optional)\n251:     - `template`: container template object\n252:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n253:   - Verify: `kubectl apply -f` succeeds\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## Phase 10: Chart Validation\n258: \n259: - [ ] **T10.1** Run `helm lint`\n260:   - Command: `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n261:   - Fix all errors and warnings\n262:   - Verify: No lint errors\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T10.2** Run `helm template`\n265:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis.default.svc:6379\"`\n266:   - Verify: All templates render without errors\n267:   - Verify: Generated YAML is valid\n268: \n269: - [ ] **T10.3** Test conditional rendering (Volcano disabled)\n270:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=false`\n271:   - Verify: No Volcano resources in output\n272:   - Verify: WorkloadManager and Router present\n273: \n274: - [ ] **T10.4** Test conditional rendering (Volcano enabled)\n275:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n276:   - Verify: Volcano ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, Deployment present\n277:   - Verify: Volcano ClusterRole and ClusterRoleBinding present\n278: \n279: - [ ] **T10.5** Test conditional rendering (Router RBAC enabled)\n280:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true`\n281:   - Verify: Router ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding present\n282: \n283: - [ ] **T10.6** Test values overrides\n284:   - Test replica overrides: `--set router.replicas=3 --set workloadmanager.replicas=2`\n285:   - Test resource overrides: `--set router.resources.limits.cpu=1000m`\n286:   - Test image overrides: `--set router.image.repository=myregistry/router`\n287:   - Verify: Overrides apply correctly in rendered templates\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Phase 11: E2E Testing (Optional/Kind Cluster)\n292: \n293: - [ ] **T11.1** Create Kind cluster\n294:   - Command: `kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e`\n295:   - Verify: Cluster is running\n296: \n297: - [ ] **T11.2** Install chart\n298:   - Command: `helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --create-namespace --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\"`\n299:   - Verify: Installation succeeds\n300: \n301: - [ ] **T11.3** Verify Deployments\n302:   - Wait for WorkloadManager: `kubectl wait deployment/workloadmanager --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m`\n303:   - Wait for Router: `kubectl wait deployment/agentcube-router --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m`\n304:   - Verify: Both deployments available\n305: \n306: - [ ] **T11.4** Verify Services\n307:   - Command: `kubectl get svc -n agentcube`\n308:   - Verify: workloadmanager and agentcube-router services exist\n309: \n310: - [ ] **T11.5** Verify RBAC\n311:   - Command: `kubectl get clusterrole/workloadmanager`\n312:   - Command: `kubectl get clusterrolebinding/workloadmanager`\n313:   - Verify: RBAC resources exist\n314: \n315: - [ ] **T11.6** Test upgrade with optional components\n316:   - Command: `helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true --set router.rbac.create=true`\n317:   - Verify: Upgrade succeeds\n318:   - Verify: Volcano deployment created\n319:   - Verify: Router RBAC created\n320: \n321: - [ ] **T11.7** Cleanup\n322:   - Command: `kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e`\n323:   - Verify: Cluster deleted\n324: \n325: ---\n326: \n327: ## Acceptance Criteria\n328: \n329: 1. ✅ Chart structure complete: `Chart.yaml`, `values.yaml`, `.helmignore`\n330: 2. ✅ All templates render without errors (`helm template`)\n331: 3. ✅ `helm lint` passes with no errors or warnings\n332: 4. ✅ Redis secret created with correct password encoding\n333: 5. ✅ WorkloadManager Deployment has correct env vars, probes, resources\n334: 6. ✅ Router Deployment has `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` constructed correctly\n335: 7. ✅ WorkloadManager RBAC: ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n336: 8. ✅ Router RBAC: conditional, namespace-scoped Role + RoleBinding\n337: 9. ✅ Volcano Scheduler: conditional, full scheduling stack\n338: 10. ✅ CRDs: AgentRuntime (existing) and CodeInterpreter (new) valid\n339: 11. ✅ Conditional rendering works for optional components\n340: 12. ✅ Values overrides work for multi-environment support\n341: 13. ✅ `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n342: 14. ✅ All deployments become available\n343: 15. ✅ RBAC permissions correctly scoped\n344: 16. ✅ Service ports and selectors correctly configured\n345: 17. ✅ Helper templates work consistently across all manifests\n346: 18. ✅ Labels follow Kubernetes conventions (`app.kubernetes.io/*`)\n347: 19. ✅ Security contexts configured (Volcano runs as non-root)\n348: 20. ✅ Health check endpoints match component implementations\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: **Notes:**\n353: - Stage ST-0: Implementation pending\n354: - Redis password: stored in Secret, referenced via `secretKeyRef`\n355: - WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: constructed dynamically from release namespace\n356: - Router RBAC: disabled by default, enable via `router.rbac.create: true`\n357: - Volcano Scheduler: disabled by default, enable via `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n358: - CRDs: installed in `crds/` directory (Helm 3 convention, installed before templates)\n\n(End of file - total 358 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values Tasks\n\n**Module:** manifests  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-0 (pending)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Chart Metadata & Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create `Chart.yaml`\n  - Set `apiVersion: v1`\n  - Set `name: agentcube`\n  - Set `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n  - Set `version: 0.1.0`\n  - Set `appVersion: \"1.0.0\"`\n  - Add keywords: `agent`, `sandbox`, `kubernetes`, `volcano`\n  - Add maintainers and home/sources metadata\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775880389726,"end":1775880389762}}}}
