ils/http.py`\n33:   - Import `requests`, `HTTPAdapter`, `Retry`\n34:   - Implement `create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10, max_retries=0)`\n35:   - Configure retry strategy with `backoff_factor=0.1`, `status_forcelist=[429, 500, 502, 503, 504]`\n36:   - Mount `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`\n37:   - Return configured `requests.Session`\n38:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n39:   - Verify: Session has adapters mounted for http/https with correct pool sizes\n40: \n41: - [x] **T1.5** Create `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n42:   - Implement `read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str`\n43:   - Return file contents stripped\n44:   - Return `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`\n45:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n46:   - Verify: Returns empty string for missing file, stripped content for existing\n47: \n48: - [x] **T1.6** Create `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n49:   - Implement `get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO)`\n50:   - Create logger with stream handler\n51:   - Format: `%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s`\n52:   - Avoid duplicate handlers\n53:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py`\n54:   - Verify: Logger outputs formatted messages\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Phase 2: Control Plane Client ✓\n59: \n60: - [x] **T2.1** Create `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n61:   - Import all three client classes: `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n62:   - Define `__all__` with client names\n63:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n64:   - Verify: Clients importable from `agentcube.clients`\n65: \n66: - [x] **T2.2** Create `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n67:   - Import `ControlPlaneClient`, `os`, `requests`, utilities\n68:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n69:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n70: \n71: - [x] **T2.3** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__()`\n72:   - Parameters: `workload_manager_url`, `auth_token`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n73:   - Resolve `base_url` from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env\n74:   - Raise `ValueError` if URL missing\n75:   - Resolve auth token from arg or service account file\n76:   - Create session with `create_session()`\n77:   - Set headers: `Content-Type`, optional `Authorization`\n78:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n79:   - Verify: Instantiates with URL, uses env fallback, handles missing token gracefully\n80: \n81: - [x] **T2.4** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`\n82:   - Parameters: `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `metadata=None`, `ttl=3600`\n83:   - POST to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n84:   - JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata`\n85:   - Timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n86:   - Return `response.json()[\"sessionId\"]`\n87:   - Raise `ValueError` if `sessionId` missing\n88:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n89:   - Verify: Returns session ID from mock response\n90: \n91: - [x] **T2.5** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`\n92:   - Parameter: `session_id: str`\n93:   - DELETE to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n94:   - Return `True` on success or 404\n95:   - Return `False` on other errors (log warning)\n96:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n97:   - Verify: Idempotent on 404, logs on error\n98: \n99: - [x] **T2.6** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.close()`\n100:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n101:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n102:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## Phase 3: Data Plane Clients ✓\n107: \n108: - [x] **T3.1** Create `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n109:   - Import `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, dependencies\n110:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n111:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n112: \n113: - [x] **T3.2** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__()`\n114:   - Parameters: `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`, `base_url`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n115:   - Resolve `base_url`: use provided OR compute from `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name`\n116:   - Raise `ValueError` if can't resolve\n117:   - Create session, set `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n118:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n119:   - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, session header set\n120: \n121: - [x] **T3.3** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient._request()`\n122:   - Parameters: `method`, `endpoint`, `body=None`, `**kwargs`\n123:   - Build URL with `urljoin(self.base_url, endpoint)`\n124:   - Set `Content-Type: application/json` if body present\n125:   - Apply timeout from kwargs or defaults\n126:   - Return `requests.Response`\n127:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n128:   - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n129: \n130: - [x] **T3.4** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()`\n131:   - Parameters: `command: Union[str, List[str]]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n132:   - Convert string command to list\n133:   - Build JSON body: `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`\n134:   - Apply read timeout buffer: `timeout_value + 2.0`\n135:   - POST to `api/execute`\n136:   - Raise `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n137:   - Return `stdout` string\n138:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n139:   - Verify: Returns stdout, raises on non-zero exit\n140: \n141: - [x] **T3.5** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.run_code()`\n142:   - Parameters: `language: str`, `code: str`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n143:   - Support `python`, `py`, `python3`\n144:   - Write timestamped `.py` file via `write_file()`\n145:   - Execute via `python3 <file>` using `execute_command()`\n146:   - Raise `ValueError` for unsupported languages\n147:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n148:   - Verify: Python code executes correctly\n149: \n150: - [x] **T3.6** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.write_file()`\n151:   - Parameters: `content: str`, `remote_path: str`\n152:   - Base64 encode content\n153:   - POST JSON to `api/files`: `path`, `content`, `mode=\"0644\"`\n154:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n155:   - Verify: File created via base64 encoding\n156: \n157: - [x] **T3.7** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file()`\n158:   - Parameters: `local_path: str`, `remote_path: str`\n159:   - Read local file as binary\n160:   - POST multipart to `api/files` with `file`, `path`, `mode`\n161:   - Set `x-agentcube-session-id` header explicitly\n162:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n163:   - Verify: Multipart upload succeeds\n164: \n165: - [x] **T3.8** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.download_file()`\n166:   - Parameters: `remote_path: str`, `local_path: str`\n167:   - Clean path: `remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n168:   - GET from `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`\n169:   - Write chunks to local file\n170:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n171:   - Verify: File downloaded correctly\n172: \n173: - [x] **T3.9** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.list_files()`\n174:   - Parameter: `path: str = \".\"`\n175:   - GET from `api/files` with query `path`\n176:   - Return JSON response\n177:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n178:   - Verify: Returns file list\n179: \n180: - [x] **T3.10** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close()`\n181:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n182:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n183:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n184: \n185: - [x] **T3.11** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n186:   - Import `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`, dependencies\n187:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n188:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n189: \n190: - [x] **T3.12** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__()`\n191:   - Parameters: `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n192:   - Compute `base_url` from `router_url` + namespace + agent_name path using `urljoin()`\n193:   - Create session with `create_session()`\n194:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n195:   - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, connection pool configured (10/10)\n196: \n197: - [x] **T3.13** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`\n198:   - GET from `self.base_url`\n199:   - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n200:   - Raise `ValueError` if header missing\n201:   - Return session ID\n202:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n203:   - Verify: Extracts session ID from response header\n204: \n205: - [x] **T3.14** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()`\n206:   - Parameters: `session_id`, `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n207:   - Set headers: `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n208:   - Apply timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` or instance default\n209:   - POST JSON payload to `self.base_url`\n210:   - Return `requests.Response`\n211:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n212:   - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n213: \n214: - [x] **T3.15** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close()`\n215:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n216:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n217:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Phase 4: Configura